John Petersen says in March 2016, explaining why Support won't install it on CSE Linux machines:
The Linux version of Skype is in a severely neglected state.  It hasn't been updated in almost 2 years, is still 32-bit, and requires too many old compatibility libraries which are a bloat on the OS.  Additionally, the ancient version has broken functionality now, no longer able to connect to clients running OS X and Windows:
https://www.google.com/search?q=skype+for+linux&ie=utf-8&oe=utf-8#q=skype+for+linux&tbm=nws

===========================================================================

In case of an authentication failure when logging in (signing in), the
problem may be at skype.com.  For example, you could check whether
forum.skype.com is available (though any such check is not completely
authoritative).

