UW CSE:

[Dynamic version did not work on F19 or F22!  :-( ]
I get: bash: /homes/gws/mernst/bin/Linux-x86_64/skype: /lib/ld-linux.so.2: bad ELF interpreter: No such file or directory


# Navigate to http://www.skype.com/download/skype/linux/choose/
# The Fedora version is an RPM, which I don't have the permissions to
# install, so use the standard dynamic version.

VER=skype-4.3.0.37
cd ~/bin/install
tar xjf ${VER}.tar.bz2
cd $HOME/bin/`uname`-`uname -m`
\ln -sf ../install/${VER}/skype .

See email of 1/2009 with Jan Stanislow for audio setup for godwit

# As of 12/2011, both static and dynamic versions give me the error:
#   skype: error while loading shared libraries: libasound.so.2: cannot open shared object file: No such file or directory
# If I do
#   export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=${LD_LIBRARY_PATH}:/lib64
# then I get
#   skype: error while loading shared libraries: libasound.so.2: wrong ELF class: ELFCLASS64

# Static version:
VER=skype_static-2.2.0.35
cd ~/bin/install
tar xjf ${VER}.tar.bz2
cd $HOME/bin/`uname`-`uname -m`
\ln -sf ../install/${VER}/skype .

