Useful page:
http://www.skype.com/help/guides/soundsetup_linux.html

skype: no audio in or out
  Textual output:
  read error, res = -1 , handle = 26

# For KDE
artsdsp skype
  can hear, but mic does not seem to work.
artsdsp -m skype
  can hear, but mic does not seem to work
  

# For Gnome
esddsp skype 
  esddsp: command not found


Verify that mic and headphones are working with
  rec ~/tmp/hello.wav
  play ~/tmp/hello.wav

===========================================================================

Instructions from http://linuxmafia.com/faq/Debian/alsa.html :

sudo apt install alsa-base alsa-headers alsa-modules-`uname -r` alsa-oss alsa-utils alsamixergui 

Choose card named "intel8x0"

(alsamixer says that the card is "Cirrus Logic CS4299 rev 6")

in alsamixer, turn on "mic boost" channel:  use arrows to get to it, then
type "m".

===========================================================================

Skype customer service says:

  Inconsistent SkypeOut account balances

  To remedy this problem, please select "Log off" from File menu and then
  "Log in as a New User" from the File menu. Type in your username and
  password and click next. After successful login, you are able to place
  calls.

  Please note that closing Skype and running the Skype client again is not
  the same as logging off.

